# NX Workspace Conventions

## Commands — use NX, not raw npm/yarn

| Instead of      | Use                          |
| --------------- | ---------------------------- |
| `npm run build` | `nx run {project}:build`     |
| `npm run test`  | `nx run {project}:test`      |
| `npm run lint`  | `nx run {project}:lint`      |
| Build all       | `nx run-many --target=build` |
| Test affected   | `nx affected --target=test`  |

## Dependency analysis — NX MCP first

1. If NX MCP available: `get_project_graph`, `get_affected_projects`, `get_project_details`
2. Fallback CLI: `nx graph --file=output.json`, `nx affected --dry-run`, `nx show project {name}`

Do not manually trace import chains or read package.json scripts.

## Module boundaries

NX enforces `@nx/enforce-module-boundaries` via ESLint.
Check `tags` and `depConstraints` before proposing cross-library imports.

## Cache

NX caches build/test/lint outputs. Do not re-run unnecessarily. Cached runs are valid.

## Docker targets — use NX, not raw docker

| Instead of              | Use                                             |
| ----------------------- | ----------------------------------------------- |
| `docker build -t app .` | `nx run {project}:docker-build`                 |
| `docker push app:tag`   | `nx run {project}:docker-push`                  |
| Build changed images    | `nx affected --target=docker-build --base=main` |

Check `nx show project {name}` for Docker target existence before running.

## Generators

Use `nx g @nx/{plugin}:{generator} {name}` for new libs/apps.
Do not create `project.json`, `tsconfig.json`, or `jest.config.ts` manually.

## Release

Use `nx release` for version bumping and changelog. Not manual CHANGELOG.md edits.
